<exercise checkit-seed="0040" checkit-slug="E1" checkit-title="Linear systems, vector equations, and augmented matrices">
  <statement>
    <p> Consider the system of equations
            <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 4 "><mrow>-2 \, x_{1} &amp;+&amp; 3 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 3 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 6</mrow><mrow>-3 \, x_{1} &amp;+&amp; 4 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 6 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 7</mrow><mrow>-x_{1} &amp; &amp;  &amp;+&amp; 6 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; -2</mrow><mrow>x_{1} &amp;-&amp; x_{2} &amp;-&amp; 3 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 3</mrow></md></p>
    <ol>
      <li> Write an augmented matrix corresponding to this system. </li>
      <li> Write a vector equation corresponding to this system. </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
-2 &amp; 3 &amp; 3 &amp; 6 \\
-3 &amp; 4 &amp; 6 &amp; 7 \\
-1 &amp; 0 &amp; 6 &amp; -2 \\
1 &amp; -1 &amp; -3 &amp; 3
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me> x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-3 \\
-1 \\
1
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
4 \\
0 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
6 \\
6 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
6 \\
7 \\
-2 \\
3
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

